			      | TRISTANIA3D EASTER EGGS |
			      +-------------------------+


 The traditional definition of an Easter Egg, like the ones that kids look for at 
Easter time, are little treasures that are valuable and surprise you when you find 
them. They don't have to be simply references to movies, games or otherwise, but 
neat things that you will be surprised upon viewing. Tristania3D also has some Easter 
Eggs hidden here and there - if you look for them eagerly, you shall eventually find 
them.

General Eggs:
=============

This very file is also an Easter Egg - whether you've find it by viewing the game 
mapfiles, or just dilly-dallying around with the data files - you have stumbled across 
this document. And if you have reached this part of the document, you might encourage 
reading it more.

During the game, if you stand still for 1 minute, Einar Moen will show something 
with his hand - and not the sign of peace.


1: Preludium
------------

¤ The background music for the level was also used in the very first level of the 
very first Doom - E1M1: Hangar (ID Software PC game), symbolizing that this is where 
it all begun, and there will be a lot to come. This is a direct reference for Doom, 
and the "great beginnings" style.

¤ The level title is a direct reference to the Tristania song with the same title.


